title: Week 5 college football: Three biggest takeaways - College Football
text:
by Colin Becht Twitter Email Posted: Sun Oct. 4, 2015 Three and out: Takeaways from Week 5 of College Football College football's Week 5 muddied the race for the College Football Playoff, with four Top 10 teams losing and No. 1 and 2 both escaping with narrow victories. Another week of upsets and close calls has shaken up what we thought we knew and brought new teams to the forefront of races for conference titles and College Football Playoff berths.
Here are the three biggest takeaways from Week 5:
1. Itâ€™s starting to feel like 2007
The 2007 season was famous for its chaotic nature that by the end of the regular season left no undefeated teams and only one one-loss team. The 2015 season has a long way to go to reach that level of pandemonium, but the early signs are there.
College Football Ohio State holds off Indiana, but Buckeyes remain vulnerable by Colin Becht
